<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-062-136 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 253 617</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Sept 9 1991 n437 pS9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Palmtop's small grip; product limitations preventing big growth.andO;(Computer Retail Week Supplement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Quick, Greg.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The palmtop computer market is experiencing steady growth, but thepaucity of applications and poor marketing have kept these smallmachines from experiencing spectacular growth.andP;  Makers of palmtopssuch as Poqet Computer Corp and Hewlett-Packard say that mostretail outlets are unsure of how to sell the palmtops, as acalculator or computer, and that salespeople remain uneducatedabout the capabilities of palmtops.andP;  Those in the retail sectorcounter by saying that the real problem with the machines is alack of applications.andP;  Some palmtops are really only useful aselectronic organizers for business users.andP;  HP claims there arehundreds of software developers writing applications for itsHP95LX Palmtop PC, and that they should start being availablebefore the end of 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Marketing StrategySoftware SelectionMarket AnalysisHand-held computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>